##### <span id="index"></span>Reporting

The IBIS Reporting feature enables the export of tabular (IBIS) data to
CSV, HTML or JSON.  
Report data is provided by reporting modules. 4 modules are available:

-   Microsoft SQL Server
-   PowerShell
-   LDAP
-   [IBIS](#Module_IBIS)
-   [Parameters](#Report_Parameters)

###### Location

All reporting functionality is available through the *Reporting* link in
the *All pages* menu or by directly entering *\[IBIS URL\]/Reporting* in
the browser address bar. Please be aware that the page is only visible /
accessible when the user has read permission to it.

</figure>

Administrators (users who are a member of the IBIS\_Administrators role)
will see all available reports with options and an *Add new report*
button. Regular users will only see the reports they are authorized for
with a *Generate report* link.

###### Generate a report

To generate a report or access it's options, hover over the report and
click on the **Generate report** link.

###### Global connections

To access the reporting global connections menu, click the connections
button on the top right of the main screen. More information on global
connections can be found in section [Global
connections](#globalconnections).

###### Querylizer

To access the querylizer tool, click the querylizer button on the top
right of the main screen. More information on querylizer can be found in
section [Querylizer](#querylizer).

# Report definitions

A report definition is a placeholder for:

-   Report metadata (name, description, etc.)
-   Module configuration
-   Authorization
-   Audit information (separately stored with reference to report
    identifier)

When a report definition is removed, all of the above will be removed as
well except for the audit information.

## Creating a new report definition

-   To create a new report, click on the *Add new report* button in the
    reporting main screen. A sidepanel with the following layout will
    appear:

<figure class="figure mb-5">
<img
src="data:image/png;base64,"
class="figure-img img-fluid rounded" />
<figcaption>Add new report sidepanel.</figcaption>
</figure>

-   Provide a name for the new report. This name will be visible by end
    users who have permission to generate this report.
-   Select the module which provides the data for the report. After the
    new report is saved, the module type cannot be changed.
-   Click the *Add* The new report will be added to IBIS and is visible
    in the main screen.

#### Report definition properties

Report definition properties can only be edited by an IBIS
administrator. To so so, hover over the desired report in the reporting
main screen and click the settings link.

A sidepanel with all available report options will open:

###### Permissions

The permissions tab contains a list of roles who are authorized to
generate the report.

To add a new permission:

-   Double click anywhere on the background of the right side of the
    panel
-   In the new row that appears, select an IBIS role you wish to
    authorize
-   Save the report definition

To remove an existing permission:

-   Hover over the permission you want to remove
-   Click the trash icon on the right
-   Save the report definition

###### Default values for export

This tab contains all available settings for all export modules.
Changing a value will result in this value being set by default when
generating a report. This may come in handy when, for example, a CSV
report always needs to be separated by a comma instead of a semicolon.

###### Delete

The delete tab contains the button which permanently removes the report
definition from IBIS.

This action is irreversible and will delete everything except audit
information.

# Global connections<span id="globalconnections"></span>

Global connections can be used to set connection properties once and
reuse them in multiple report definitions. This way you dont have to
update multiple reports when for example a password changes.

## Creating a global connection

-   Click the power plug button on the top left of the reporting screen.
    A sidepanel will open showing the available connections:

<figure class="figure mb-5">
<img
src="data:image/png;base64,"
class="figure-img img-fluid rounded" />
</figure>

-   Click the *Add* button. The following panel will show up:

<figure class="figure mb-5">
<img
src="data:image/png;base64,"
class="figure-img img-fluid rounded" />
</figure>

-   Provide a displayname for the connection
-   Specify the type of reporting module this connection serves
-   Click the *Add* button to add the connection to the system

## Modify global connection properties

-   Click the power plug button on the top left of the reporting screen.
    A sidepanel will open showing the available connections:

<figure class="figure mb-5">
<img
src="data:image/png;base64,"
class="figure-img img-fluid rounded" />
</figure>

-   Click on the name of the connection you wish to modify. The
    following panel will show up (settings will vary depending on the
    selected module type):

<figure class="figure mb-5">
<img
src="data:image/png;base64,"
class="figure-img img-fluid rounded" />
</figure>

-   Change the settings according to your needs
-   Click the *Save and close* button to save the settings to database

### Modules

<span id="Module_IBIS"></span>

##### IBIS

The IBIS module returns IBIS data straight from the database.

The module supports object-level authorization for the following types:

-   AliasDossier
-   ApplicationDossier
-   EpicDossier
-   FmsDossier
-   Group
-   IDossier
-   IdentityDossier
-   PbsDossier
-   TgDossier
